The paper discusses a novel algorithm for real-time behavior change detection in streaming data. This involves processing high-speed real-time data and continuously learning from it to detect anomalies in a single pass of data. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). However, given the focus on developing a new algorithm for behavior change detection, Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) are the most likely sub-categories.
